cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on the effectiveness of randomized defenses against adversarial samples in the context of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the security of these defenses against different types of attackers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification, which falls under the scope of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of deep learning models and the evaluation of their performance against adversarial attacks also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experiments and analysis of results, which could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
